<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 2:41PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of south central Moore,
Scotland, Anson and Richmond Counties through 345 PM EDT...
At 239 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms capable of producing winds of 40 mph. Storm movement
was southeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Laurinburg, Rockingham, Wadesboro, Hamlet, Maxton, Ansonville,
Hoffman, Polkton, Ellerbe and Foxfire.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
